This paper deals with methods to compute dense vector embeddings for documents in a corpus, given a set of word vectors. This is a common problem in natural language processing and information retrieval, which falls under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions an evaluation task using TripAdvisor reviews, which suggests a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV) for sentiment analysis or image captioning.
